headline: Three Reasons to Avoid TXN and One Stock to Buy Instead
summary: Texas Instruments currently trades at $200.25 per share and has shown little upside over the past six months, posting a middling return of 2.7%. The stock also fell short of the S&P 500’s 14.2% gain during that period.
